  "text": "The CODEOWNERS infrastructure in grafana/grafana consists of the following components:\n\n1. **The CODEOWNERS file**: `.github/CODEOWNERS` — the GitHub ownership definition that maps file patterns to owning teams/users.\n\n2. **CI workflow for validation**: `.github/workflows/codeowners-validator.yml` — a GitHub Actions workflow triggered on PRs to main that uses the `mszostok/codeowners-validator` action to run checks (files, duppatterns, syntax, notowned, avoid-shadowing).\n\n3. **Manifest generation scripts** (JavaScript) in `scripts/codeowners-manifest/`:\n   - `index.js` — main orchestration entry point\n   - `generate.js` — generates the manifest files\n   - `metadata.js` — generates metadata from CODEOWNERS\n   - `raw.js` — generates raw CODEOWNERS data\n   - `constants.js` — shared constants for the manifest scripts\n   - `README.md` — documentation for the manifest system\n   - `scripts/test-coverage-by-codeowner.js` — script for running test coverage reports grouped by codeowner team\n\n4. **Go type definition**: `pkg/services/featuremgmt/codeowners.go` — defines the `codeowner` string type used in feature management, along with all the team constants (e.g., `grafanaAlertingSquad`, `identityAccessTeam`, etc.).\n\n5. **npm scripts**: Defined in `package.json` under the `scripts` section:\n   - `codeowners-manifest` — runs `node ./scripts/codeowners-manifest/index.js`\n   - `codeowners-manifest:clean` — cleans and recreates the manifest directory\n   - `codeowners-manifest:generate` — runs generate.js\n   - `codeowners-manifest:metadata` — runs metadata.js\n   - `codeowners-manifest:raw` — runs raw.js\n   - `test:coverage:by-codeowner` — runs the full manifest generation then coverage script\n\n6. **Jest config**: `jest.config.codeowner.js` — a Jest configuration that reads the generated CODEOWNERS manifest to scope test runs and coverage collection to files owned by a specific team (via `TEAM_NAME` environment variable)."
